<paragraph blockId="48.[151,712,263,352]" box="[151,712,263,287]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,294,263,287]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Type-species</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authority="Lamarck, 1818" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1818" box="[308,712,264,287]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Galeolaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="caespitosa">
<emphasis box="[308,544,264,287]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Galeolaria caespitosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lamarck, J. B. de" box="[550,712,264,287]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" pagination="274 - 374" refId="ref63255" refString="Lamarck, J. B. de (1818) Histoire Naturelle des animaux sans vertebres, presentant ... Part 5. Deterville and Verdiere, Paris, 612 pp. [Annelides, 274 - 374]." type="book chapter" year="1818">Lamarck, 1818</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,712,263,352]" box="[151,378,296,319]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Number of species: 2</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,712,263,352]" box="[151,158,329,352]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">.</paragraph>
<caption pageId="48" pageNumber="49" startId="48.[151,255,1792,1816]" targetBox="[187,1399,382,1757]" targetPageId="48">
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,1792,1922]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1792,1816]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">FIGURE 21.</emphasis>
SEM micrographs of chaetae in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1818" box="[667,906,1793,1816]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Galeolaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="caespitosa">
<emphasis box="[667,906,1793,1816]" italics="true" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Galeolaria caespitosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Australia, Sydney, Port Jackson, intertidal, Th. Mortensen's Pacific Expedition 14-16, exchange Zoological Museum Copenhagen, ZMA V.Pol. 3637. A—bundle of collar chaetae, B—detail of thoracic limbate chaeta, C—1 
<superScript attach="left" box="[805,815,1863,1875]" fontSize="5" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">st</superScript>
row of thoracic uncini, D—anterior abdominal uncini, E—details of anterior abdominal chaeta with a hollow tip.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1436,1969,2033]" lastBlockId="49.[151,1436,152,835]" lastPageId="49" lastPageNumber="50" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
Tube white or pink, opaque, with 2 longitudinal keels, trapezoidal in cross-section. Granular overlay absent. Operculum rather flat ampulla with distal calcareous plate, armed with elaborate movable spines. Peduncle thick, triangular in cross-section, with distal wings; inserted almost medio-dorsally, covering the base of up to 3–4 dorsal radioles; constriction absent. Pseudoperculum absent. Radioles arranged almost in spirals (1.25 whorl), up to 42 per lobe. Stylodes and branchial eyes absent. Inter-radiolar membrane present. Mouth palps absent. 7 thoracic chaetigerous segments. Collar trilobed, collar edge entire, smooth, occasionally with frilly edge (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Morch" authorityYear="1863" box="[224,337,306,331]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Galeolaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hystrix">
<emphasis box="[224,337,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">G. hystrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Tonguelets absent. Thoracic membranes forming apron. Collar chaetae small, limbate (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="48.[151,255,1792,1816]" captionTargetBox="[187,1399,382,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-118@48.[163,1414,364,1781]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 21. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Galeolaria caespitosa. Australia, Sydney, Port Jackson, intertidal, Th. Mortensen's Pacific Expedition 14-16, exchange Zoological Museum Copenhagen, ZMA V.Pol. 3637. A—bundle of collar chaetae, B—detail of thoracic limbate chaeta, C—1st row of thoracic uncini, D—anterior abdominal uncini, E—details of anterior abdominal chaeta with a hollow tip." pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 21A</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Philippi" authorityYear="1844" box="[227,344,345,370]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Apomatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[227,344,345,370]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Apomatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
chaetae absent. Thoracic uncini saw-shaped with 7–10 teeth, anterior peg stout, rounded to spatulate (
<figureCitation box="[273,383,384,410]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="48.[151,255,1792,1816]" captionTargetBox="[187,1399,382,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-118@48.[163,1414,364,1781]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 21. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Galeolaria caespitosa. Australia, Sydney, Port Jackson, intertidal, Th. Mortensen's Pacific Expedition 14-16, exchange Zoological Museum Copenhagen, ZMA V.Pol. 3637. A—bundle of collar chaetae, B—detail of thoracic limbate chaeta, C—1st row of thoracic uncini, D—anterior abdominal uncini, E—details of anterior abdominal chaeta with a hollow tip." pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 21C</figureCitation>
). Triangular depression absent. Abdominal chaetae true trumpet-shaped, smoothly bent, with two rows of denticles separated by a hollow groove and extended into a long lateral spine (
<figureCitation box="[1315,1423,422,448]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="48.[151,255,1792,1816]" captionTargetBox="[187,1399,382,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-118@48.[163,1414,364,1781]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 21. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Galeolaria caespitosa. Australia, Sydney, Port Jackson, intertidal, Th. Mortensen's Pacific Expedition 14-16, exchange Zoological Museum Copenhagen, ZMA V.Pol. 3637. A—bundle of collar chaetae, B—detail of thoracic limbate chaeta, C—1st row of thoracic uncini, D—anterior abdominal uncini, E—details of anterior abdominal chaeta with a hollow tip." pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 21E</figureCitation>
). Abdominal uncini with 11–15 teeth, anterior peg stout, rounded (
<figureCitation box="[927,1036,461,487]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="48.[151,255,1792,1816]" captionTargetBox="[187,1399,382,1757]" captionTargetId="figure-118@48.[163,1414,364,1781]" captionTargetPageId="48" captionText="FIGURE 21. SEM micrographs of chaetae in Galeolaria caespitosa. Australia, Sydney, Port Jackson, intertidal, Th. Mortensen's Pacific Expedition 14-16, exchange Zoological Museum Copenhagen, ZMA V.Pol. 3637. A—bundle of collar chaetae, B—detail of thoracic limbate chaeta, C—1st row of thoracic uncini, D—anterior abdominal uncini, E—details of anterior abdominal chaeta with a hollow tip." pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Fig. 21D</figureCitation>
), posterior ones rasp-shaped with 2–3 rows. Long posterior capillary chaetae absent. Achaetous anterior abdominal zone short (2–3 segments). Posterior glandular pad absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="49" pageNumber="50" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,152,835]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,319,576,602]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1818" box="[457,585,577,602]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Galeolaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[457,585,577,602]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Galeolaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the taxa that has been attributed to Savigny by various authors (e.g., 
<bibRefCitation author="Fauchald, K." box="[218,456,616,642]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 188" refId="ref58220" refString="Fauchald, K. (1977) The polychaete worms. Definitions and keys to the orders, families and genera. Natural History Museum of Los Angeles County Science Series, 28, 1 - 188." type="journal article" year="1977">Fauchald 1977: 144</bibRefCitation>
). The Code, however, is very clear on the point of priority of publication, 
<bibRefCitation author="Lamarck, J. B. de" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="274 - 374" refId="ref63255" refString="Lamarck, J. B. de (1818) Histoire Naturelle des animaux sans vertebres, presentant ... Part 5. Deterville and Verdiere, Paris, 612 pp. [Annelides, 274 - 374]." type="book chapter" year="1818">Lamarck (1818)</bibRefCitation>
precedes 
<bibRefCitation author="Savigny, J. C." box="[346,530,654,680]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="3 - 128" refId="ref67200" refString="Savigny, J. C. (1820) Systeme des Annelides, principalement de celles des cotes de l'Egypte et de la Syrie, offrant les caracteres tant distinctifs que naturels des ordres, familles et genres, avec la description des especes. Description de l'Egypte, Histoire Naturelle, Paris I (3), l'Imprimerie Royale: 3 - 128." type="journal article" year="1820">Savigny (1820)</bibRefCitation>
, and is the author of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1818" box="[776,904,655,680]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Galeolaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[776,904,655,680]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Galeolaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Fauchald, K." box="[959,1195,654,680]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" refId="ref58258" refString="Fauchald, K. (1992) A review of the genus Eunice (Polychaeta: Eunicidae) based upon type material. Smithsonian Contributions to Zoology 523, x + 422 pp." type="book" year="1992">Fauchald 1992: 2–3</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1436,152,835]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1818" box="[334,463,693,718]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Galeolaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[334,463,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Galeolaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the southern half of 
<collectingCountry box="[896,1003,693,719]" name="Australia" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Australia</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[1067,1232,693,719]" name="New Zealand" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1818" box="[1246,1406,693,718]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Galeolaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="caespitosa">
<emphasis box="[1246,1406,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">G. caespitosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is gregarious and intertidal, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Morch" authorityYear="1863" box="[561,674,732,757]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Galeolaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hystrix">
<emphasis box="[561,674,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">G. hystrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is solitary and subtidal, rarely forming “reefs” (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Smith, A. M. &amp; McGourty, C. R. &amp; Kregting, L. &amp; Elliot, A." pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1297 - 1304" refId="ref67543" refString="Smith, A. M., McGourty, C. R., Kregting, L. &amp; Elliot, A. (2005) Subtidal Galeolaria hystrix (Polychaeta, Serpulidae) reefs in Paterson Inlet, Stewart Island, New Zealand. New Zealand Journal of Marine and Freshwater Research, 39, 1297 - 1304." type="journal article" year="2005">
Smith 
<emphasis box="[1376,1436,732,757]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">et al.</emphasis>
2005
</bibRefCitation>
). The uncorroborated records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1818" box="[599,859,770,795]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Galeolaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="caespitosa">
<emphasis box="[599,859,770,795]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Galeolaria caespitosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[931,1113,770,796]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fauvel, P." box="[1157,1321,770,796]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 107" refId="ref58524" refString="Fauvel, P. (1947) Annelides polychetes de Nouvelle-Caledonie et des iles Gambier. Faune Empire Francais, 8, 1 - 107." type="journal article" year="1947">Fauvel (1947)</bibRefCitation>
and of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Morch" authorityYear="1863" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Galeolaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="hystrix">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">G. hystrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from N.W. 
<collectingCountry box="[370,437,809,835]" name="Spain" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Spain</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Alvarino, A." box="[481,671,809,835]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref55233" refString="Alvarino, A. (1951) Incrustaciones marinas. Boletin del Instituto Espanol de Oceanografia 45, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1951">Alvariño (1951)</bibRefCitation>
are most probably erroneous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1279,886,951]" box="[151,1169,886,912]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
1. 
<taxonomicName authority="Lamarck, 1818" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityYear="1818" box="[180,627,886,912]" class="Polychaeta" family="Serpulidae" genus="Galeolaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Sabellida" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="caespitosa">
<emphasis box="[180,440,887,912]" italics="true" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Galeolaria caespitosa</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lamarck, J. B. de" box="[447,627,886,912]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50" pagination="274 - 374" refId="ref63255" refString="Lamarck, J. B. de (1818) Histoire Naturelle des animaux sans vertebres, presentant ... Part 5. Deterville and Verdiere, Paris, 612 pp. [Annelides, 274 - 374]." type="book chapter" year="1818">Lamarck, 1818</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, temperate and cold southern part of 
<collectingCountry box="[1062,1169,886,912]" name="Australia" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">Australia</collectingCountry>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="49.[151,1279,886,951]" box="[151,1279,925,951]" pageId="49" pageNumber="50">
